<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — elloloop" description="elloloop privacy policy — how we collect, use, and protect your data.">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { day: 'numeric', month: 'long', year: 'numeric' })}</em></p>

    <p>
      Welcome to elloloop. This Privacy Policy explains how ELLOLOOP LTD ("we", "us", or "our") collects, 
      uses, shares, and protects your personal information when you use our website (elloloop.com), our 
      learning platforms (including EasyLoops and Tortoise Learning), and our related mobile applications 
      and services (collectively, the "Services").
    </p>

    <h2>1. Data Controller Information</h2>
    <p>
      ELLOLOOP LTD is the data controller responsible for your personal data. 
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Company Name:</strong> ELLOLOOP LTD</li>
      <li><strong>Company Number:</strong> 13414108</li>
      <li><strong>Registered Office:</strong> 14 Featherstone Road, London, England, NW7 2BN</li>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@elloloop.com">info@elloloop.com</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect information to provide and improve our Services. This includes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account Data:</strong> When you register, we collect your name, email address, and authentication credentials (which may include OAuth data from third-party login providers).</li>
      <li><strong>Profile and Usage Data:</strong> Information about your interactions with our Services, including learning progress, code submissions, quiz results, and preferences.</li>
      <li><strong>Device and Technical Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, device identifiers, and operating system information used to access our Services.</li>
      <li><strong>Communications:</strong> If you contact us for support, we keep a record of that correspondence.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We process your personal data under the following lawful bases:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Performance of a Contract:</strong> To create your account, provide our educational services, and ensure our platforms function correctly.</li>
      <li><strong>Legitimate Interests:</strong> To improve our Services, analyze usage trends, ensure security, and prevent fraud.</li>
      <li><strong>Consent:</strong> When you opt-in to receive marketing communications or consent to specific data processing activities.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Artificial Intelligence (AI) Processing</h2>
    <p>
      Our Services utilize AI to provide personalized feedback and tutoring. Code submissions, questions, 
      and learning interactions may be processed by third-party AI providers (such as OpenAI or Google). 
      We do not use your personal identifiable information (PII) to train these third-party foundational models.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data Sharing and Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share your information with trusted service providers who assist us in operating our Services, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Cloud hosting and infrastructure providers (e.g., Google Cloud, Firebase).</li>
      <li>Authentication services to manage secure logins.</li>
      <li>Analytics providers to help us understand how our Services are used.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These third parties are contractually obligated to safeguard your data and only process it according to our instructions.</p>

    <h2>6. Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, 
      including any legal, accounting, or reporting requirements. 
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Account Deletion:</strong> You have the right to delete your account and associated data at any time. 
      You can initiate account deletion directly through the account settings within our mobile applications and web platforms, 
      or by contacting us at <a href="mailto:info@elloloop.com">info@elloloop.com</a>. Upon deletion, your personal data will 
      be securely removed or anonymized.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your GDPR Data Protection Rights</h2>
    <p>Under the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR), you have the following rights:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>The right to access:</strong> You can request copies of your personal data.</li>
      <li><strong>The right to rectification:</strong> You can request that we correct inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
      <li><strong>The right to erasure:</strong> You can request that we erase your personal data, under certain conditions.</li>
      <li><strong>The right to restrict processing:</strong> You can request that we restrict the processing of your data.</li>
      <li><strong>The right to object to processing:</strong> You can object to our processing of your personal data.</li>
      <li><strong>The right to data portability:</strong> You can request that we transfer your data to another organization or directly to you.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:info@elloloop.com">info@elloloop.com</a>. We have one month to respond to your request.</p>

    <h2>8. International Data Transfers</h2>
    <p>
      Your data may be transferred to, and processed in, countries outside of the UK and European Economic Area (EEA). 
      When we do so, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place (such as Standard Contractual Clauses) to protect your information.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Security</h2>
    <p>
      We implement robust, industry-standard security measures, including encryption in transit and at rest, 
      to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for legal reasons. 
      We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the new policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Complaints</h2>
    <p>
      If you have concerns about our use of your personal data, you can make a complaint to us at <a href="mailto:info@elloloop.com">info@elloloop.com</a>. 
      You can also complain to the ICO (Information Commissioner's Office) if you are unhappy with how we have used your data:
    </p>
    <p>
      Information Commissioner’s Office<br />
      Wycliffe House, Water Lane<br />
      Wilmslow, Cheshire, SK9 5AF<br />
      Helpline number: 0303 123 1113<br />
      Website: <a href="https://www.ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.ico.org.uk</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
